The 42nd session of the Human Rights Council

   6 September 2019
   | Human Rights

   The 42nd session of the Human Rights Council will be held in Geneva
   from Monday 9 September to Friday 27 September 2019.

   Global Health and Foreign Policy Initiative - Ministerial Communiqué

Global Health and Foreign Policy Initiative - Ministerial Communiqué

   27 August 2019
   | France at the UN

   France holds the chairmanship of the Foreign Policy and Global Health
   Initiative, which brings together seven countries: South Africa,
   Brazil, France, Indonesia, Norway, Senegal and Thailand. The health
   ministers of the seven (...)

   World Humanitarian Day

World Humanitarian Day

   19 August 2019
   | Humanitarian and Human Rights | International Days

   On World Humanitarian Day, France pays tribute to all humanitarian aid
   workers. Their commitment is more than ever necessary as we face
   greater needs, longer crises and increasing violations of international
   humanitarian (...)

   70 years of the Geneva Conventions

70 years of the Geneva Conventions

   12 August 2019
   | Humanitarian and Human Rights | International Days

   The four Geneva Conventions were adopted 70 years ago today. They are
   at the heart of international humanitarian law: they allow to save
   lives and limit the barbarity of war.
